Client: Cigna, Austin TX
July2018- Oct,2018
Role: Sr. UI/UX developer & Designer
Sravankumar.tangella@Cigna.com
Responsibilities:
• Extensive experience of Object Oriented JavaScript design pattern and JavaScript MVC Patterns Preferably Angular JS.
• Interacted with clients to understand their existing applications and design the site according to their system requirements.
• Developed the user interface with HTML, HTML5, CSS, CSS3, JavaScript, jQuery, Bootstrap, Angular Js
• Used Responsive Web Design templates to meet cutting-edge technology requirements.
• Implemented Page Optimization techniques for web pages, Best Practices in JavaScript and handled Cross Browser compatibility issues in web pages.
• Developed prototype concepts using Invision Studios concept designs
• Managed internationally based engineers, analysts & testers on various Adobe Experience cloud projects.
• Researched, strategized and launched UX improvements.
• Developed a cross-platform mobile app using Ionic and Cordova.
• Used Angular2.x to bind HTML elements data to JavaScript Objects and developed dynamic Single Page Application (SPA's).
• Developed Custom Directives like Elements, Attributes and Classes and AngularJS2 .x Factory to monitor asynchronous service calls through Dependency Injection
• Extensively implemented ES6 for building interactive cross platform web application and optimizing the application for high performance
• Developing custom HTML elements using Angular2 directives.
Implemented Angular2.x classes and life cycle hooks to maintain the data present in each view.
• Used IBM Bluemix to build, test, and deploy the applications.
• Automated Build and deployment pipeline using GIT, Maven and Jenkins.
• Involved in localization and internationalization of the web pages using JSON and Angular 2
• Developed JS applications on MVC based frameworks like Angular MVC.
Environment: HTML, CSS3, JavaScript, Angular Js, Eclipse, Adobe Experience Manager, Bootstrap, Ionic, Cordova, Ajax, DOM, Node JS, GIT,
